INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(38,1783326519.0,1.78333781388620448e+09,'build','Wire congruency''s tag/form engine to render the tracker DB: a <<<TicketList>>> Tag_Interface class (invocators/tags/dev/, modeled on BugReport.php) that reads project.db/the ledger and renders the ticket table; a validated ticket-submission form via Path A (forms rows: type RadioSelect + description TextBox + FCE->?page=ticketDone; a TicketLogger handler tag modeled on OrdererTag; a TicketDAO copy of OrderDAO writing a tickets table with an in_array allowlist check); page Documents ?page=tickets/ticketDone in the dev seed. Dogfoods the CMS + is the dead-code-audit vehicle (#6).','medium','CLOSED','Wire congruency''s tag/form engine to render the tracker DB: a <<<TicketList>>> Tag_Interface class (invocators/tags/dev/, modeled on BugReport.php) that reads project.db/the ledger and renders the ticket table; a validated ticket-submission form via Path A (forms rows: type RadioSelect + description TextBox + FCE->?page=ticketDone; a TicketLogger handler tag modeled on OrdererTag; a TicketDAO copy of OrderDAO writing a tickets table with an in_array allowlist check); page Documents ?page=tickets/ticketDone in the dev seed. Dogfoods the CMS + is the dead-code-audit vehicle (#6). [DONE this session] Tag/form engine renders the tracker DB: TicketList (list) + TicketForm/TicketLogger (native submission). tagcheck 29/29.','{"orig_id": 14, "type": "build", "source": "tracker-ledger", "orig_status": "open"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(39,1783327391.0,1.78333781388620448e+09,'build','Persist gate memories in the DB: new memories(id,ts,session,tool,intent,note) table in project.db, written by the gate (store.record_memory) stamped with CLAUDE_CODE_SESSION_ID so tool-use history persists AS sessions; JSON log demoted to emergency fallback; gate__query gains session filter (+''current''). Promotes project.db to ONE persistent install db at ~/.MCP/project.db ($PROJECT_DB override), NOT the disposable working-tree copy, since memories aren''t ledger-rebuildable. Backfilled legacy gate-memories.json; retired repo-local project.db.superseded; SIGNALS.md updated.','medium','CLOSED','Persist gate memories in the DB: new memories(id,ts,session,tool,intent,note) table in project.db, written by the gate (store.record_memory) stamped with CLAUDE_CODE_SESSION_ID so tool-use history persists AS sessions; JSON log demoted to emergency fallback; gate__query gains session filter (+''current''). Promotes project.db to ONE persistent install db at ~/.MCP/project.db ($PROJECT_DB override), NOT the disposable working-tree copy, since memories aren''t ledger-rebuildable. Backfilled legacy gate-memories.json; retired repo-local project.db.superseded; SIGNALS.md updated. [DONE this session] memories(id,ts,session,tool,intent,note) table + MemoryList view; gate persists via store->jazz.','{"orig_id": 15, "type": "build", "source": "tracker-ledger", "orig_status": "active"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(40,1783333224.8475,1.78333790788299608e+09,'design','Filed via headless chromium through the native forms engine','medium','CLOSED','Filed via headless chromium through the native forms engine [closed] This was the first live ticket submitted through the native form (a demo artifact), not backlog.','{"source":"web-form","type":"design"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(41,1.78333387829015183e+09,1.78333387829015183e+09,'build','Nav: replace home/about with Pages + Tags views','medium','CLOSED','PageList tag renders the ?page=pages index of all Documents; TagList tag renders ?page=tags gallery of all invocator tags as hyperlinks, each rendering the tag. SiteMap nav updated. Implemented + verified in headless chromium.','{"source": "user-suggestion"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(42,1.78333387829015183e+09,1.78334560201479482e+09,'build','Remove the order wizard entirely','low','CLOSED','Nav link already removed (SiteMap blocklists config/order/thanks). Remaining: decide whether to delete the config/order/thanks Documents and the OrderForm/Orderer/OrderDAO code (currently retained as the order-form model that TicketForm/TicketLogger/TicketDAO were based on). [progress] Order-wizard PAGES removed (config/order/thanks Documents + templates). Remaining: the OrderForm/Orderer/OrderDAO lib code + tags stay for now as the model TicketForm/TicketLogger/TicketDAO were based on. [audit #30] Safe scope: delete only the 6 order-wizard TAG files (page-less); KEEP lib Order* (bugs-page demo + admin depend on it). [DONE] Removed the 5 page-less order-wizard TAG files; kept Config_Form_Invocator (code-referenced by Catalog_Controller) and ALL lib Order*/ConfigForm (bugs-page demo + admin depend on them). Gates green.','{"source": "user-suggestion"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(43,1.78333387829015183e+09,1.78334611958466696e+09,'research','Categories as a tagging system to group pages/threads','medium','OPEN','Use the Categories table (already present, empty) as a tagging system: tag pages/threads with one or more categories and browse by category. Note a CategoryView tag already exists in invocators/tags. Design: category schema/link table, tagging UI, and a category-browse view.

Clarification: ''specifications'' is a concrete example CATEGORY/tag for pages — pages get tagged with one or more categories (e.g. ''specifications'') and are browsed/grouped by category. Categories act as the tag layer for pages (and later threads). [progress] Page_Categories link table + specifications category added; CategoryPages browse tag built and wired into ?page=pages. [progress] Tagging UI shipped: TagPageForm (DbSelect page + category) -> TagPageHandler inserts Page_Categories; browse by category live at ?page=pages. Remaining: extend categories to threads; category admin (create/rename). [note] Core shipped this session; remainder is optional enhancement.','{"source": "user-suggestion"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(44,1.78333387829015183e+09,1.78336913758070397e+09,'build','Forms: add more form elements','medium','CLOSED','The forms engine currently supports TextField, TextBox, RadioSelect, FormConfigElement, ConfigForm* variants. Add more element types (e.g. select/dropdown, checkbox/multi-select, number, date, hidden, file) with validation, produced from the forms table via FormElementBean::produceElement. [progress] Added DbSelect: a DB-backed <select> form element (options from ''pages''/''categories'' queries, with option-set = allowlist validation). First new element type; more to follow (checkbox/multiselect/number/date). [progress] Two new elements shipped+tested: DbSelect (DB-backed dropdown) and Checkbox (boolean, urgent->high on TicketForm). Remaining: number/date/multi-select. [note] Core shipped this session; remainder is optional enhancement. [progress] Added NumberField (numeric input + min/max range validation; JSON-round-trippable via extraFromArray re-derive). Elements now: TextField/TextBox/BigTextBox/RadioSelect/Checkbox/DbSelect/FormConfigElement/NumberField. Remaining optional: date/multi-select. [progress] Added DateField (ISO date input + min/max range validation). Remaining optional: multi-select. [#44 CLOSED] Full form element set: TextField, TextBox, BigTextBox, RadioSelect, Checkbox, DbSelect, FormConfigElement, NumberField, DateField, MultiSelect. This session added NumberField (numeric+min/max), DateField (ISO+min/max), MultiSelect (array-valued+allowlist) on top of DbSelect/Checkbox; all JSON-round-trippable (#45) + gated by tools/formelement_roundtrip.php (18 cases).','{"source": "user-suggestion"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(45,1.78333387829015183e+09,1.7833680876825881e+09,'build','Forms: better deserialization technique for the POM/session','high','CLOSED','The form/POM state is persisted across requests via PHP serialize()/__wakeup into $_SESSION[''POM'']. Replace with a more robust, portable technique (e.g. explicit JSON (de)serialization of form results) so form state survives class changes and is inspectable; reduces reliance on __wakeup class-reloading.
[PLAN #45 — POM serialize()→JSON]
Surface: PersistentObjectManager::pack/unpack store the POM via PHP serialize() into $_SESSION[''POM'']
(PersistentObjectManager.php ~L41-42) and StandardForm::__wakeup reloads element classes on unserialize.
Plan (one element type per crank, keep old path until all converted):
 1. Add to_array()/from_array() to StandardForm and each form-element class (RadioSelect, TextBox, TextField, DbSelect,
    Checkbox, FormConfigElement) — plain data, no behavior.
 2. Change PersistentObjectManager to json_encode a registry [{type, data}] into $_SESSION[''POM''] and json_decode+rebuild
    on load (dispatch by type via the tag/class loader), replacing serialize/__wakeup.
 3. Test EACH step by driving the multi-step ticket form + tag/category forms in headless chromium — the FCE action/oncomplete
    flow depends on results surviving the session round-trip, so verify getResults() still returns after Continue->Continue. [crank 1 DONE] AbstractFormElement.to_array/from_array (base fields, extra* hooks, circular form ref excluded) + RadioSelect + tools/formelement_roundtrip.php gate. Remaining elements: TextBox, TextField, BigTextBox, DbSelect, Checkbox, FormConfigElement; then StandardForm (composes element arrays); then flip POM pack/unpack serialize->JSON + chromium form test. serialize() still live. [crank 2 DONE] TextBox verified covered by base (no per-class hooks); gate case added. Remaining: TextField, BigTextBox, DbSelect, Checkbox, FormConfigElement, StandardForm. [crank 3 DONE] TextField base-covered; gate case added. Remaining: BigTextBox, DbSelect, Checkbox, FormConfigElement, StandardForm. [crank 4 DONE] BigTextBox base-covered; gate case. Remaining: DbSelect (own state), Checkbox, FormConfigElement, StandardForm. [crank 5 DONE] DbSelect: extraFromArray re-derives options from elementString; gate defines CONGRUENCY_SQLITE from install.json. Remaining: Checkbox, FormConfigElement, StandardForm. [crank 6 DONE] Checkbox base-covered; gate case. Remaining: FormConfigElement, StandardForm. [crank 7 DONE] FormConfigElement base-covered (config re-parsed from elementString). All 6 elements + FCE JSON-serializable. Remaining: StandardForm, then PAUSE for greenlight on the pack/unpack flip. [crank 8 DONE — SAFE PHASE COMPLETE] StandardForm JSON-serializable. All 6 elements + FCE + StandardForm now have to_array/from_array; gate 8/8. Remaining: the RISKY flip of PersistentObjectManager::pack/unpack serialize()->JSON registry + drop StandardForm::__wakeup, needs chromium form verification — PAUSED for human greenlight. [#45 CLOSED] POM form persistence moved serialize()->JSON. All 6 elements+FCE+StandardForm+FormManager have to_array/from_array (gate 9/9); POM pack/unpack use JSON envelopes with serialize-fallback for non-form objects (ClassLoader/Document/etc); StandardForm::__wakeup dropped. Verified end-to-end in chromium (ticket + tag/category forms). Form state is now inspectable JSON and survives class changes.','{"source": "user-suggestion"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(46,1.78333387829015183e+09,1.78334611958466696e+09,'build','Tag test harness: rendered vs predicted, logged as tickets (with bet predictions)','medium','OPEN','Build a harness that, for every tag under invocators/tags, records a PREDICTED rendering as a `bet` ticket, then renders the tag (standalone, as ?page=tags&tag=NAME does) and compares rendered result vs predicted. Log each outcome as a ticket (pass/fail), and provide a view. Model on the tournament predictions harness (predict.py / predictions.jsonl). Uses ticket types: bet (prediction) + test (result). [progress] tools/tagcheck.py added (renders every tag, asserts 200 + no PHP error). It refuted the all-pass bet and surfaced bug #58. Next: predicted-output bets per tag. [progress] tagcheck drove the shim-STDERR fix (#58 closed) and surfaced bug #60 (Content::__toString null). [green] tag-render harness passes 29/29 after fixing #58 + #60. [note] Core shipped this session; remainder is optional enhancement.','{"source": "user-suggestion"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(47,1.78333506595094275e+09,1.7833364370172646e+09,'build','REST interface for every table','medium','CLOSED','Generic REST layer over every table in the unified DB. Read-only first increment SHIPPED: boot/rest.php, dispatched by router.php on ?api= — ?api=tables (discovery), ?api=<table> (paginated JSON), ?api=<table>&id=<pk> (single row); table name allowlisted against sqlite_master. Follow-up: writes (POST/PUT/DELETE) with validation + auth, and a REST view/console. Precedent: the tracker ticket.py REST + human view. [progress] REST CREATE (POST) shipped + tested (column-validated insert). Remaining: UPDATE (PUT) and DELETE by id, plus auth. [done] Full REST CRUD (GET/POST/PUT/DELETE) shipped + tested; pk-protected, column-validated, single-row writes. Auth still a follow-up.','{"source": "user-suggestion"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(48,1.78333582398241901e+09,1.78333586506313633e+09,'bet','PREDICTION: TagList re-entrancy guard fixes the tag-gallery recursion','high','CLOSED','Crank: added a static \$rendering guard to TagList so selecting ?page=tags&tag=TagList no longer renders itself recursively. PREDICTION: the crawler will now report broken=1 (only the deliberate ?page=nope demo), down from 3 — ?page=tags&tag=TagList and &tag=TagPageHandler both become HTTP 200. Refuted if either is still HTTP None. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — crawler: broken 3->1; TagList & TagPageHandler now HTTP 200; only the deliberate ?page=nope demo remains. Bet won; no bug report.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(49,1.78333586506313633e+09,1.78333790788299608e+09,'documentation','Documentation pass (end-of-day)','medium','CLOSED','Last queued item for today. Document the CMS additions this session: the tag catalog (TicketList/MemoryList/SiteMap/PageList/TagList/CategoryPages + handlers), the native forms flow (FCE action -> handler via FORM_MANAGER), DbSelect element, Page_Categories tagging, the REST layer (boot/rest.php, ?api=), tools/crawl.py, and the unified ~/.jazz DB shape. Update SIGNALS.md/README as needed. [DONE] Wrote checkouts/current/doc/CMS_ADDITIONS.md covering pages/tags/forms/elements/categories/REST/tools + the unified DB shape + remaining backlog.','{"source": "user-suggestion"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(50,1.78333608701026225e+09,1.78333612482877111e+09,'bet','PREDICTION: removing order-wizard pages leaves no dangling links','medium','CLOSED','Crank on #42: delete the config/order/thanks Documents + templates 6/7/8. PREDICTION: crawler valid-pages 14->11; broken stays 1 (only ?page=nope); NO new broken links (SiteMap/PageList regenerate from remaining Documents). Refuted if broken>1. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — valid pages 14->11, broken stays 1, no dangling links.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(51,1.78333622365353775e+09,1.78333627625181102e+09,'bet','PREDICTION: REST POST creates a row (columns validated)','medium','CLOSED','Crank on #47: added POST create to rest.php. PREDICTION: POST /?api=tickets with a JSON body returns 201 + rowid and GET ?api=tickets total increases by 1; unknown columns are ignored (not in ''used''). Refuted if total unchanged or a bogus column is written. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — 201 + rowid, tickets 51->52, bogus column ignored.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(53,1.78333635190443587e+09,1.78333643688882327e+09,'bet','PREDICTION: REST PUT updates a row by id','low','CLOSED','Crank #47: PUT ?api=tickets&id=X sets fields; updated=1, GET reflects change, pk untouched. Refuted otherwise. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — updated=1, GET reflects change, pk (id) protected.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(55,1.78333643688882327e+09,1.7833364370172646e+09,'bet','PREDICTION: REST DELETE removes a row by id','low','CLOSED','Crank #47: DELETE ?api=tickets&id=X removes exactly that row; deleted=1, GET id -> 404. Refuted otherwise. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — deleted=1, GET id -> 404.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(57,1.78333668715545701e+09,1.78333678520317626e+09,'bet','PREDICTION: every tag renders cleanly via the tag-check harness','medium','CLOSED','Crank #46 (first increment): tools/tagcheck.py renders each tag standalone (?page=tags&tag=NAME) and asserts HTTP 200 with no Fatal/Parse/Uncaught/"error:" in the output. PREDICTION: all tags PASS (0 failures) after the TagList recursion fix. Refuted if any tag errors. [RESULT] REFUTED — 2 of 29 tags fail: BodyTag, Catalog_Controller leak an uncaught PHP fatal when rendered standalone. Harness works; bug filed.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(58,1.78333678520317626e+09,1.7833371168155539e+09,'bug','shim.php:45 uses STDERR (undefined under php -S web SAPI) -> uncaught fatal','medium','CLOSED','Rendering these tags standalone in the gallery (?page=tags&tag=NAME) leaks an UNCAUGHT PHP fatal into the 200 response (TagList''s try/catch does not stop it). Found by tools/tagcheck.py.
  reproduce: GET /?page=tags&tag=BodyTag  and  /?page=tags&tag=Catalog_Controller
  BodyTag: Fatal error</b>: Uncaught Error: Undefined constant &quot;STDERR&quot; in /home/notificationsforsteven/big-jazz-main/packages/congruencey/checkouts/current/boot/shim.php:45 Stack t
  Catalog_Controller: Fatal error</b>: Uncaught Error: Undefined constant &quot;STDERR&quot; in /home/notificationsforsteven/big-jazz-main/packages/congruencey/checkouts/current/boot/shim.php:45 Stack t
  likely cause: these need request/page context (or are not standalone-renderable tags); the fatal is an Error type not caught, or thrown outside get_document(). Fix options: (a) filter non-standalone tags out of the gallery, or (b) harden TagList to render each sub-tag in an output-buffered, shutdown-guarded sandbox. [ROOT CAUSE] boot/shim.php:45 references the STDERR constant, which is only defined in the CLI SAPI, not under php -S. Any path reaching it fatals; BodyTag/Catalog_Controller trigger it. FIX: guard with defined(''STDERR'') or use error_log() / php://stderr. Small, safe next crank. [FIXED] shim.php:45 now uses error_log() (SAPI-portable). Verified: the ''Undefined constant STDERR'' fatal is gone; the tags now fail with a DIFFERENT, deeper error (Content::__toString null) -> filed separately.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bug", "found_by": "tagcheck.py"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(59,1783337031.60154,1.7833371168155539e+09,'bet','PREDICTION: STDERR guard fixes bug #58 (all tags render clean)','medium','CLOSED','Crank: shim.php:45 fwrite(STDERR) -> error_log(). PREDICTION: tools/tagcheck.py now 0 failures (29/29 pass); tools/crawl.py still broken<=1. Refuted if BodyTag/Catalog_Controller still fatal. [RESULT] REFUTED — tagcheck still 2 FAIL, but the cause changed (STDERR fixed; Content::__toString now surfaces). crawl broken=1 (no regression). Onion peeled one layer.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(60,1.7833371168155539e+09,1.78333736519128108e+09,'bug','Content::__toString() returns null (type error) at lib/Content/Content.php:25','medium','CLOSED','Surfaced after fixing bug #58. When content is unset, Content::__toString() returns \$this->content (null), violating the string return type -> Uncaught TypeError. Hit by BodyTag/Catalog_Controller when a shim query yields no content.
  reproduce: GET /?page=tags&tag=BodyTag
  fix: `return \$this->content ?? '''';` (one line). [FIXED] Content::__toString returns content ?? ""; TypeError gone; all 29 tags render clean.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bug", "found_by": "tagcheck.py"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(61,1.78333730929639887e+09,1.78333736519128108e+09,'bet','PREDICTION: Content __toString null-guard clears the TypeError','medium','CLOSED','Crank #60: Content::__toString returns content ?? "". PREDICTION: the Content TypeError is gone for BodyTag/Catalog_Controller; tagcheck failures drop (0, or a deeper distinct error surfaces = onion); crawl broken<=1. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — tagcheck 29/29 pass, BodyTag clean, no new layer, crawl broken=1.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(62,1.78333762170349764e+09,1.78333773604399395e+09,'bet','PREDICTION: Checkbox element + urgent field -> high-severity ticket','medium','CLOSED','Crank #44: new Checkbox element; TicketForm gains optional ''urgent''; TicketLogger maps urgent->severity high. PREDICTION: submitting the ticket form with urgent CHECKED creates a ticket with severity=''high''; tagcheck stays all-pass; crawl broken<=1. Refuted if severity!=high or a form/render error. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — checkbox renders, urgent->severity high (ticket #63), tagcheck 29/29, crawl broken=1.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(64,1.78334424635952782e+09,1.78334448185385179e+09,'bet','PREDICTION: gpl_stamp finds few/zero missing headers; my new files pass','low','CLOSED','Crank #29: tools/gpl_stamp.py checks every .php for the GPL short-notice. PREDICTION: this session new files (tags/rest/elements/tools) all PASS; any missing are legacy; --fix stamps them; tagcheck 29/29 + crawl broken<=1 unchanged after fix. [RESULT] count REFUTED (66 missing, not few) but tool works + my new files all passed. Caught+fixed a line-ending (CRLF->LF) bug in the stamper IN TEST before commit; re-stamp is insertions-only, endings preserved, harnesses green.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(65,1.78334470286887574e+09,1.78334473948012089e+09,'bet','PREDICTION: $CONGRUENCY_CONFIG loads install.json from outside the install folder','low','CLOSED','Crank #27: configure.php reads getenv(CONGRUENCY_CONFIG) else <deploy-root>/install.json. PREDICTION: with CONGRUENCY_CONFIG=<external path> the app reports CONGRUENCY_SQLITE from the EXTERNAL file (/srv/external/marker.sqlite); with it unset, the default checkouts/current/install.json (~/.jazz). Refuted otherwise. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — external config read (/srv/external/marker.sqlite); default falls back to checkouts/current/install.json (~/.jazz).','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(66,1.78334494612887024e+09,1.78334499111391067e+09,'bet','PREDICTION: README CMS section added, harnesses unaffected','low','CLOSED','Crank #28: add a Run-the-live-CMS section to checkouts/current/README.md referencing doc/CMS_ADDITIONS.md, serve.py, pages, REST (?api=), tools, config-as-data + $CONGRUENCY_CONFIG; note PDO pending #25. PREDICTION: README updated, doc/CMS_ADDITIONS.md exists, tagcheck 29/29 + crawl broken<=1 unaffected (README not served). [RESULT] CONFIRMED — README CMS section added; gates green (29/29, broken=1).','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(67,1.78334519615998291e+09,1.78334524827795362e+09,'bet','PREDICTION: ~6 tags used only via the gallery + Order* lib candidate-dead; 0 orphan pages','low','CLOSED','Crank #30 audit. PREDICTION: 0 orphan pages (PageList links all Documents); ~6 tag classes not referenced by any real page template (only reachable via the TagList gallery), notably the order-wizard tags after config/order/thanks removal; the lib Order* classes they wrap are candidate-dead. [RESULT] REFUTED (count) — 17 gallery-only tags (not ~6); Order* is NOT dead (referenced by the bugs demo + admin). Valuable finding, no bug.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(68,1.78334555379999351e+09,1.78334560201479482e+09,'bet','PREDICTION: delete 5 page-less order tags (keep Config_Form_Invocator, code-referenced)','medium','CLOSED','Crank #42: grep showed Config_Form_Invocator is emitted by Catalog_Controller (<<<Config_Form_Invocator($product)>>>) -> KEEP it. Delete the other 5 (OrderFormTag, OrdererTag, ConfigFormTag, Order_Form_Invocator, Orderer_Invocator) — only comment refs. PREDICTION: tagcheck 29->24 all-pass; crawl broken<=1; no template/code emits the 5 deleted tags (no dangling). lib untouched. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — deleted 5 order tags, tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken=1, no functional dangling (only a doc-comment, tidied). Config_Form_Invocator kept (Catalog_Controller emits it).','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(69,1783345851.60399,1.78334587606657838e+09,'bet','PREDICTION: install_signals.py syncs repo->~/.MCP identically','low','CLOSED','Crank #37: tracker/install_signals.py copies tracker/signals-mcp/server.py -> ~/.MCP/signals-mcp/server.py. PREDICTION: after running, the two files are byte-identical (filecmp) and --check reports in-sync. Refuted if mismatch. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — synced identical; --check reports in-sync.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(70,1.78335490335168981e+09,1.78335502233611059e+09,'bug','BUG-06: Tag_Wrapper::execute_all_tags has no recursion guard (DoS)','high','CLOSED','The tag engine recurses into each tag''s rendered output with no depth/visited guard, so a document whose Title is <<<TitleTag>>> (or any self-emitting tag) loops forever. Already bit us via TagList. Engine-level fix: a depth cap. [FIXED] depth cap (>=64 -> stop expanding) added to Tag_Wrapper::execute_all_tags. Engine-level fix; the earlier TagList guard remains as a fast-path.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bug", "ref": "BUG-06"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(71,1.78335490335168981e+09,1.78335502233611059e+09,'bet','PREDICTION: depth cap 64 stops BUG-06 recursion, legit nesting unaffected','high','CLOSED','Crank: add a depth cap (>=64 -> stop expanding) to Tag_Wrapper::execute_all_tags. PREDICTION: a Document titled <<<TitleTag>>> now renders BOUNDED (returns within a 5s timeout, no hang); tagcheck stays 24/24 and crawl broken<=1 (real nesting is <=~6, well under 64). Refuted if it still hangs or a page breaks. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — <<<TitleTag>>>-titled doc renders bounded (0.018s, 3924B, HTTP 200), no hang; gates green (24/24, broken=1).','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet", "fixes": 70}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(72,1.78335525432153201e+09,1.78335546983387374e+09,'bet','PREDICTION: __toString checker flags 3 (ClassLoader, CommandRegistry, AbstractDAO); fixing clears them','medium','CLOSED','Sweep of the #60 null-return class. tools/tostring_check.py flags __toString methods that can return non-string (no return, or a bare return of a NULL-initialized var). PREDICTION: flags exactly 3 (ClassLoader, CommandRegistry, AbstractDAO); literal ones (CommandTemplate/Redirect/DestroySession) + fixed Content pass. After init NULL->"" / add return "", checker=0, php -l clean, tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken<=1. [RESULT] count REFUTED (7, not 3 — checker beat manual): +CategoryList/ProductList/PriceList/PriceDAO. All 7 fixed (NULL-init->"", empty stubs->return ""); checker=0, php -l clean, gates green. The reusable tools/tostring_check.py is now a gate.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet", "ref": "BUG-04/#60-class"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(73,1.78335567972235751e+09,1.78335583432624983e+09,'bug','BUG-04: AbstractDAO::returnAllBeans returns null on empty (should be [])','medium','CLOSED','returnAllBeans inits $beansArray=NULL and only fills in-loop; a zero-row query returns NULL. Callers current()/iterate it -> TypeError/warning (the live current() caller CatalogDAO::obtainRow is commented, but the contract is wrong and FormElementDAO relies on !empty guards). Fix: init array(). [FIXED] returnAllBeans inits array(); zero-row result now returns [] not null.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bug", "ref": "BUG-04"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(74,1.78335567972235751e+09,1.78335583432624983e+09,'bet','PREDICTION: returnAllBeans NULL->array() makes empty return [] (current() safe)','medium','CLOSED','Crank: init $beansArray=array(). PREDICTION: a standalone returnAllBeans(0) returns array() (was NULL), current() of it is false (no TypeError); tagcheck 24/24 + crawl broken<=1 unchanged. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — repro: before=NULL+current() TypeError; after=array()+current()=false. php -l clean, all gates green, 1-line diff.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet", "fixes": 73}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(75,1.78335655597224545e+09,1.7833566495038464e+09,'bug','BUG-01: SQL injection in CatalogDAO (raw $key interpolated)','critical','CLOSED','select_products_by_category/get_product_details/get_category_details validate $key into $itemKey then interpolate the RAW $key into SQL (category=$key etc). Fix: use $itemKey + guard isset($itemKey); malicious key -> validateNumericKey NULL -> no injectable query. [FIXED] CatalogDAO 3 methods now interpolate the validated $itemKey and guard isset($itemKey). Critical SQLi closed.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bug", "ref": "BUG-01"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(76,1.78335655597224545e+09,1.7833566495038464e+09,'bet','PREDICTION: $itemKey in SQL + isset($itemKey) closes the SQLi','high','CLOSED','PREDICTION: validateNumericKey("5 OR 1=1")=NULL and validateNumericKey("5")="5"; after fix no raw $key remains in CatalogDAO SQL, a malicious key builds no injectable query; gates green. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — no raw $key in SQL; malicious keys sanitize to NULL -> guard skips -> no injectable query; valid numeric passes; gates green.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet", "fixes": 75}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(77,1.78335682517133045e+09,1.78335692024456739e+09,'bet','PREDICTION: showcase reconciled — BUG-01/04/06 show RESOLVED, sqli demo shows Blocked','low','CLOSED','Crank: add a resolved note to BUG-01/04/06 in BugReport (green badge + strikethrough + fix note) and flip BugDemo(sqli) messaging to Blocked. PREDICTION: ?page=bugs shows 3 RESOLVED badges + a Blocked sqli demo (0 injected rows); tagcheck 24/24 + crawl broken<=1. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — ?page=bugs shows 3 resolved badges + strikethrough + fix notes; BugDemo(sqli) now renders Blocked/PATCHED (0 injected rows); gates green.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(78,1.78335729516853475e+09,1.78335729516853475e+09,'bug','BUG-02: ProductDAO never opens a connection','high','CLOSED','[FIXED] Constructor omitted CreateConnection()->open(); first query derefed null. Repro: dataConnection=NULL, obtainAllRows() -> ''Call to a member function query() on null''. Fix: open the STORE connection like sibling DAOs. After: dataConnection opened; obtainAllRows() returns [] gracefully.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bug", "ref": "BUG-02"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(79,1.78335729516853475e+09,1.7833579920693531e+09,'bug','ProductDAO queries paw.product (no such sqlite table)','low','OPEN','Surfaced fixing BUG-02: ProductDAO->table=''paw.product'' (MySQL db.table notation) but the sqlite table is ''Products''; queries log ''no such table: paw.product'' and return []. Part of the MySQL->sqlite/PDO adaptation (relates #25). Low impact: ProductView is gallery-only; CatalogDAO uses the correct ''Products'' name. [TRACED] DEAD CODE — ProductDAO is only instantiated by ProductMaker/ProductMakerList (admin Makers), which have NO callers, are not tags, and are not in any page template; there is no admin page. The live catalog uses CatalogDAO (correct Products table). Not reachable in the running app; defer to whenever the admin/Maker UI is wired (or the #25 PDO/table-name pass).','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bug"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(80,1.78335741644078493e+09,1.78335760495031952e+09,'bug','BUG-03: OrderDAO::updateRow calls nonexistent insert() + bare-key delete()','high','CLOSED','updateRow(): $this->delete($rowData[key]) (bare key, not WHERE) + $this->insert($rowData) (no such method; it is insertRow). Fix: deleteRow($rowData[key]) + insertRow($rowData). [FIXED] updateRow uses deleteRow()/insertRow().','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bug", "ref": "BUG-03"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(81,1.78335741644078493e+09,1.78335760495031952e+09,'bet','PREDICTION: updateRow->deleteRow/insertRow removes the undefined-method fatal','medium','CLOSED','PREDICTION: before, updateRow throws Call to undefined method ...insert(); after, no undefined-method fatal (delete+insert run); gates green. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — before: DELETE bare-key syntax error + undefined method insert(); after: updateRow OK (deleteRow+insertRow). NB: repro wrote to real orders table (17 empty artifacts) -> cleaned back to seed 0. gates green.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet", "fixes": 80}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(82,1.78335774942685461e+09,1.78335774942685461e+09,'bug','BUG-05: missing page crash (get_class(null))','medium','CLOSED','[VERIFIED-RESOLVED] setData uses is_object() guard; DocumentManager falls back to invalid. Missing page -> no fatal (crawler + direct test).','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bug", "ref": "BUG-05", "resolution": "verified-preexisting"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(83,1.78335774942685461e+09,1.78335774942685461e+09,'bug','BUG-07: config constants never defined','medium','CLOSED','[VERIFIED-RESOLVED] config-as-data defines MYSQL_*, ETC, STORE_LOGIN, MYSQL_SERVER (checked via configure.php).','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bug", "ref": "BUG-07", "resolution": "verified-preexisting"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(84,1.78335846396456766e+09,1.7833585920104258e+09,'bet','PREDICTION #25 crank1: DataConnection->native PDO keeps every DAO working','high','CLOSED','Migrate DataConnection open/close/query from mysql_* to a native PDO (own sqlite:CONGRUENCY_SQLITE), returning MysqlShimResult for SELECTs (consumer contract unchanged). PREDICTION: DataConnection no longer calls mysql_connect/select_db/query/close; all pages render (crawl broken<=1), tagcheck 24/24, REST works, and a DB-backed page (?page=catalog) shows real content. Refuted if any page breaks. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — DataConnection native PDO; catalog/about/bugs render real DB content; tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken=1, REST ok.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet", "ref": "#25-crank1"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(85,1.78335881981464433e+09,1.78335895816602778e+09,'bet','PREDICTION #25 crank2: AbstractDAO native (count/foreach) keeps forms working','high','CLOSED','Migrate AbstractDAO select(mysql_num_rows->count(rs->rows)), returnAllBeans(mysql_fetch_assoc loop->foreach rs->rows), quote(mysql_real_escape_string->doubling). PREDICTION: FormElementDAO->returnAllBeans still builds forms; ?page=tickets renders the ticket form (type radios + textarea + urgent checkbox); tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken<=1. Refuted if a form/page breaks. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — ticket form (type RadioSelect NAME= uppercase + description + urgent) + tag form (DbSelect) all build via FormElementDAO->returnAllBeans; tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken=1. (Initial false-negative was a case-sensitive test check.)','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet", "ref": "#25-crank2"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(86,1.78335914414326715e+09,1.7833591990661385e+09,'bet','PREDICTION #25 crank3: DocumentDAO native keeps every page rendering','high','CLOSED','Migrate DocumentDAO.getDocumentData direct mysql_num_rows/fetch_assoc/free_result -> count(rs->rows)/rs->rows[0]/remove. PREDICTION: ?page=catalog still shows Congruency Lives, ?page=about real content, all pages 200; tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken<=1. Refuted if any page content breaks -> revert+bug. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — catalog/about/bugs/ticket-form all render; no mysql_ calls; CRs 66->66; gates green.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet", "ref": "#25-crank3"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(87,1.78335940145448064e+09,1.78335946572498917e+09,'bet','PREDICTION #25 crank4: CatalogDAO native keeps CategoryView/ProductView rendering','high','CLOSED','Uniform transform: mysql_num_rows+while -> foreach(rs->rows as $__row); mysql_fetch_assoc(rs) -> $__row; drop mysql_free_result. Keep BUG-01 $itemKey. PREDICTION: ?page=tags&tag=CategoryView and &tag=ProductView render 200 no Fatal; tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken<=1. Refuted -> revert+bug. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — 5 methods -> foreach(rows); BUG-01 itemKey intact; CategoryView/ProductView render no Fatal; tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken=1.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet", "ref": "#25-crank4"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(88,1.7833597874623661e+09,1.7833598575526092e+09,'bet','PREDICTION #25 crank5: ContentDAO native, gates stay green','high','CLOSED','Migrate ContentDAO mysql_num_rows/fetch_assoc/free_result -> foreach(rs->rows). PREDICTION: tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken<=1, ContentTag renders (?page=tags&tag=ContentTag 200 no Fatal). Refuted -> revert+bug. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — ContentDAO native (count/rows[0]); ContentTag renders; tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken=1.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet", "ref": "#25-crank5"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(89,1.78336003142885065e+09,1.78336013115420484e+09,'bet','PREDICTION #25 crank6: PriceDAO native, gates stay green','high','CLOSED','Migrate PriceDAO mysql_num_rows/fetch_assoc/free_result -> foreach(rs->rows). PREDICTION: PriceMakerControl renders (200 no Fatal); tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken<=1. Refuted -> revert+bug. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — PriceDAO native (foreach + guarded rows[0]); PriceMakerControl renders; tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken=1.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet", "ref": "#25-crank6"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(90,1.78336027069010067e+09,1.78336032341487503e+09,'bet','PREDICTION #25 crank7: UserDAO native, gates stay green','high','CLOSED','Migrate UserDAO mysql_num_rows/fetch_assoc/free_result -> foreach/rows[0]. PREDICTION: Login + ToggleLogin render (200 no Fatal); tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken<=1. Refuted -> revert+bug. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — UserDAO native (foreach; double num_rows handled); Login/ToggleLogin render; tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken=1.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet", "ref": "#25-crank7"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(91,1.78336045531449913e+09,1.78336176162839341e+09,'bet','PREDICTION #25 crank8: AbstractList native, gates stay green','high','CLOSED','Migrate AbstractList direct mysql_query/num_rows/fetch_assoc/free_result -> PDO fetchAll + count/foreach. PREDICTION: list-backed tags render (?page=tags gallery, no Fatal); tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken<=1. Refuted -> revert+bug. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — AbstractList obtainList -> DataConnection+foreach (unextended dead code, now clean); ?page=tags renders; tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken=1. Only mysql_ calls left: DataConnection::quote + mysqlReport.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet", "ref": "#25-crank8"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(92,1.78336199542716765e+09,1.78336201223582601e+09,'bet','PREDICTION #25 crank9: DataConnection quote/mysqlReport native, gates green','high','CLOSED','Replace mysql_real_escape_string->doubling, mysql_info()/mysql_error()->"". PREDICTION: no mysql_ CALLS left outside shim.php defs; ?page=catalog Congruency Lives, ticket form builds; tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken<=1. Refuted -> revert+bug. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — DataConnection quote/mysqlReport native; grep CLEAN (no mysql_ calls outside shim.php defs); catalog/ticket-form render; tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken=1.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet", "ref": "#25-crank9"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(93,1.78336203923900747e+09,1.78336219081704711e+09,'bet','PREDICTION #25 crank10: shim retired, app fully native PDO','high','CLOSED','Move MysqlShimResult out of shim.php; delete mysql_* function defs; keep minimal get_magic_quotes_gpc if still called. PREDICTION: catalog/about/tickets/bugs render + REST works; tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken<=1. Refuted -> revert all + bug + STOP. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — shim retired; ZERO mysql_ anywhere; full app verified (catalog/about/tickets/bugs/memories/REST) no fatals; tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken=1.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet", "ref": "#25-crank10"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(94,1.78336381144332432e+09,1.78336413256594014e+09,'bet','PREDICTION #26: deploy on/off/redeploy verifies end-to-end in an isolated worktree','medium','CLOSED','Run deploy.py (from main, in a linked git worktree so the source tree is untouched) against a throwaway target: ON=deploy+boot_and_verify (stub Welcome home, dev ?page=bugs gone); REDEPLOY=re-run reuses install.json + re-verifies; SERVE/OFF=--serve detaches then kill. PREDICTION: deploy exits 0 (predictions CONFIRMED), redeploy idempotent, serve up then killable; source worktree stays on HEAD 916f7b1. Refuted -> bug. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — 4/4 transitions: ON deploy verifies (stub Welcome, dev gone, exit0); SERVE up 200; OFF down; REDEPLOY idempotent (reused+exit0). Isolated worktree; source tree untouched (stayed 916f7b1).','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet", "ref": "#26"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(95,1.78336450372380208e+09,1.78336467146427345e+09,'bet','PREDICTION #45 crank1: AbstractFormElement+RadioSelect JSON round-trip preserves state','medium','CLOSED','Add to_array()/from_array() (base common fields, excl. circular form ref; subclass extraToArray/extraFromArray hooks) to AbstractFormElement + RadioSelect. Round-trip test: build RadioSelect -> to_array -> json_encode -> json_decode -> from_array -> options/id/order preserved. Live serialize() path UNTOUCHED. PREDICTION: round-trip test passes; tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken<=1, ticket form still builds. Refuted -> revert+bug. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — RadioSelect+AbstractFormElement to_array/from_array round-trip through JSON (state preserved, inspectable, form back-ref dropped); tools/formelement_roundtrip.php green; live serialize() untouched, ticket form builds, tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken=1.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet", "ref": "#45-crank1"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(96,1.78336495394323897e+09,1.78336501117019081e+09,'bet','PREDICTION #45 crank2: TextBox JSON round-trip preserves state','low','CLOSED','Add extraToArray/extraFromArray to TextBox; extend the gate. PREDICTION: gate all-PASS, tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken<=1, ticket form builds; serialize() untouched. Refuted -> revert+bug. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — TextBox has no element-specific state; base to_array/from_array covers it; gate 2/2, form builds, tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken=1.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet", "ref": "#45-crank2"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(97,1.78336518907567715e+09,1.78336522384314775e+09,'bet','PREDICTION #45 crank3: TextField JSON round-trip preserves state','low','CLOSED','Add hooks if TextField has own state (else base covers); extend gate. PREDICTION: gate all-PASS, tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken<=1, ticket form builds. Refuted -> revert+bug. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — TextField base-covered (no own state); gate 3/3, form builds, tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken=1.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet", "ref": "#45-crank3"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(98,1.78336536988943386e+09,1.78336540739807915e+09,'bet','PREDICTION #45 crank4: BigTextBox JSON round-trip preserves state','low','CLOSED','Add hooks if own state else base covers; extend gate. PREDICTION: gate all-PASS, tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken<=1, ticket form builds. Refuted -> revert+bug. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — BigTextBox base-covered; gate 4/4, form builds, tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken=1.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet", "ref": "#45-crank4"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(99,1.78336555118146038e+09,1.78336566802919745e+09,'bet','PREDICTION #45 crank5: DbSelect JSON round-trip preserves config (not re-derivable options)','medium','CLOSED','Serialize DbSelect persistent config (query/table/name/selected), not option rows; newInstanceWithoutConstructor if it queries DB. PREDICTION: gate all-PASS, tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken<=1, ticket form + ?page=pages tag form (pageId/category selects) build. Refuted -> revert+bug. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — DbSelect: options are DB-derived from elementString, re-derived on from_array (not serialized); getOptions()+extraFromArray added; gate 5/5 (options count>0), ticket+pages/category forms build, tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken=1.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet", "ref": "#45-crank5"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(100,1.78336585256854677e+09,1.78336588669450974e+09,'bet','PREDICTION #45 crank6: Checkbox JSON round-trip preserves state','low','CLOSED','Add hooks if own state else base; extend gate. PREDICTION: gate all-PASS, tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken<=1, ticket+pages forms build. Refuted -> revert+bug. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — Checkbox base-covered; gate 6/6, forms build, tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken=1.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet", "ref": "#45-crank6"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(101,1.78336603108945608e+09,1.78336608962338948e+09,'bet','PREDICTION #45 crank7: FormConfigElement JSON round-trip preserves config','low','CLOSED','Serialize FCE persistent config fields (action/oncomplete/incomplete). PREDICTION: gate all-PASS, tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken<=1, ticket+pages forms build. Refuted -> revert+bug. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — FormConfigElement config (action/oncomplete/incomplete) parsed from elementString on demand, so base covers it; round-trip re-parses correctly; gate 7/7, forms build, tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken=1.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet", "ref": "#45-crank7"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(102,1.78336627710824275e+09,1.78336647167578601e+09,'bet','PREDICTION #45 crank8: StandardForm to_array/from_array round-trips (elements+results+back-refs)','medium','CLOSED','Add to_array/from_array to StandardForm (composes element to_array; from_array rebuilds + rewires setFormObject; skip sorter). PREDICTION: gate 8/8 (results survive, 2 elements w/ classes, getId resolves, back-ref set); tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken<=1, ticket+pages forms build; serialize() untouched. Refuted -> revert+bug+STOP. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — StandardForm to_array/from_array: id-keyed formElements as element arrays, sorter skipped, from_array rebuilds via newInstanceWithoutConstructor + rewires setFormObject; gate 8/8 (results survive, 2 elements/classes, getId, back-ref->new form via reflection); ticket+pages forms build, tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken=1. serialize() UNTOUCHED.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet", "ref": "#45-crank8"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(103,1.78336746454451322e+09,1.7833680876825881e+09,'bet','PREDICTION #45 crank9 (FLIP): POM data serialize->JSON envelopes; forms survive session round-trip','high','CLOSED','Flip PersistentObjectManager pack/unpack: data via json_encode of {__type,v} envelopes (FormManager/StandardForm/plain), rebuilt on unpack; drop StandardForm::__wakeup. Keep POM shell serialize (classLoader/commandQueue). PREDICTION: headless chromium multi-step ticket form Continue->Continue completes + FCE action logs the ticket; tag+category forms work; getResults survives; gate 8/8, tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken<=1. Refuted -> revert ALL + bug + STOP. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — POM pack/unpack flipped to JSON {t,v} envelopes (FormManager/StandardForm->to_array; other objects base64(serialize) fallback); StandardForm::__wakeup removed. Headless chromium: multi-step ticket form Continue->Continue logged Ticket #104 then #105 (component=bug, title=marker) via FORM_MANAGER->getResults surviving the session round-trip + TicketLogger firing; pages/category form (DbSelect) completed at ?page=tagDone no fatal. gate 9/9, tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken=1.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet", "ref": "#45-crank9-FLIP"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(106,1.78336822054895806e+09,1.78336832072226333e+09,'bet','PREDICTION #44 crank1: NumberField element (numeric input + min/max validation)','medium','CLOSED','Add NumberField (input type=number; min/max parsed from elementString; failsExtendedValidation rejects non-numeric + out-of-range; min/max re-derived on from_array). PREDICTION: round-trip gate case passes (min/max re-derived) + validation cases (accepts in-range, rejects over-max, rejects non-numeric); php -l clean; tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken<=1 (no live form uses it yet). Refuted -> revert+bug. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — NumberField (input type=number; min/max from elementString): round-trips (min/max re-derived), validates (5 ok, 99/abc rejected), renders type=number+min/max. gate 12/12, php -l clean, tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken=1.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet", "ref": "#44-NumberField"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(107,1.7833684908379302e+09,1.78336855523837423e+09,'bet','PREDICTION #44 crank2: DateField (input type=date + ISO/min/max validation)','low','CLOSED','Add DateField (input type=date; min/max ISO dates from elementString; failsExtendedValidation rejects non-YYYY-MM-DD + out-of-range; min/max re-derived on from_array). PREDICTION: gate round-trip+validation+render pass; php -l clean; tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken<=1. Refuted -> revert+bug. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — DateField (input type=date; ISO min/max from elementString): round-trips (min/max re-derived), validates (2024-06-15 ok, 2026 out-of-range + non-ISO rejected), renders type=date+min/max. gate 15/15, php -l clean, tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken=1.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet", "ref": "#44-DateField"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(108,1.78336870608519983e+09,1.78336885933871507e+09,'bug','Content::sql_assoc_array() dereferences null when content lookup misses','medium','CLOSED','User: tags -> all tags -> body tag emits PHP warnings Trying to access array offset on null in lib/Content/Content.php:38-39. ContentDAO::lookupContent returns NULL for a missing ContentID; sql_assoc_array(NULL) then does $array_data[FIELD] on null. Fix: guard is_array($array_data). [FIXED] Content::sql_assoc_array now guards is_array($array_data) — a content-lookup miss (lookupContent->null) no longer derefs null. ?page=tags&tag=BodyTag warnings 2->0; warning sweep across 29 tags + 9 pages: NONE. Also hardened tools/tagcheck.py to flag Warning/Notice/Deprecated, not just fatals (would have caught this).','{"source": "user-report", "kind": "bug"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(110,1.78336906416099071e+09,1.78336913758070397e+09,'bet','PREDICTION #44 crank3: MultiSelect (array-valued checkbox group + allowlist validation)','low','CLOSED','Add MultiSelect (name=ID[]; options via parseRadioElementString; returnValue array; failsExtendedValidation rejects values not in option allowlist; options re-derived on from_array). PREDICTION: gate round-trip+validation+render pass; php -l clean; tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken<=1. Refuted -> revert+bug. [RESULT] CONFIRMED — MultiSelect (array-valued checkbox group; name=ID[]; option-set=allowlist): round-trips (options re-derived), validates (accepts red+green subset, rejects purple non-option), renders name=tags[]+checkbox+3 options. gate 18/18, php -l clean, tagcheck 24/24, crawl broken=1.','{"source": "ratchet", "kind": "bet", "ref": "#44-MultiSelect"}');
INSERT INTO "tickets" VALUES(111,1.78337064705311369e+09,1.78337064705311369e+09,'build','doc_watch: auto stale-documentation ticketing on code-without-doc commits','low','CLOSED','Shipped checkouts/current/tools/doc_watch.py + --install-hook post-commit hook. Trigger: commit touches a script (.php/.py) but no doc (.md/.txt). Targeted per-doc via dir->doc map; one OPEN documentation ticket per doc, deduped by meta.doc + meta.commits. Files via jazz_telemetry.open_ticket. Verified: dry-run classification (lib->ARCHITECTURE, tools->tools/README, doc-commit->none, tagcheck->CMS_ADDITIONS), live open/skip/append against a temp db, hook install+fire, frozen-tree ignore, and self-commit filed nothing (README touched).','{"source": "feature"}');
